name: Google Cloud Developers Group - Kick-Off!
description:
• What we'll do
The Google Cloud Developers Group in Dublin is kicking off with an exciting talk on Kubernetes in Google Cloud Platform for developers by David Gonzalez, a Google Developer Expert for Google Cloud.

Join us for an evening of fun talks on Google Cloud followed by pizza.
Stay tuned we are coming up with exciting events every month!

• Important to know
Please register for your free tickets on Eventbrite! We have limited seats so hurry up!
https://www.eventbrite.com/e/google-cloud-developers-group-kick-off-tickets-43713686814

name: GDG Cloud Dublin - April 2018
description:
GDG Cloud Dublin - April 2018 is our monthly meetup that offers speaker sessions across Cloud, applications, microservices, and more!

This month the talk is going to be on Chaos Engineering on Kubernetes in GCP lead by Javier Arrieta.

Javier has more than 35 years of programming experience with more than 25 years of OOP programming. He has been giving several talks on microservices, system architecture/ops, functional scala, etc. in various meetups and internal talks.

We are looking forward to meeting you at Google - Gordon House on April 19, 2018.

NOTE: Please register for your free ticket on Eventbrite! We have limited seats so hurry up!

https://www.eventbrite.com/e/gdg-cloud-dublin-april-2018-tickets-44953471042?ref=eios&aff=eios

GDG Cloud Dublin Team

name: Google I/O Extended 2018
description:
Come join us for I/O Extended 2018! -
https://events.withgoogle.com/google-io-extended-2018/

What to expect?
Talks: Googlers, Google Developer Experts and talented local developers will deliver talks on Cloud, Android, AI, Design, IOT and much more.

Live Stream: Of course no I/O Extended would be complete without a live stream of the Keynote in Mountain View.

When is it on?
I/O Extended is on from 1:30 PM on Tuesday, May 8th with the live stream starting at 6:00 PM.

Don't forget to register yourselves on the Google I/O Extended 2018 website!

We look forward to seeing you there!

name: Google DevFest 2018
description:
Dublin DevFest is in it's 6th year!

You can see all of the details and customize your schedule on our DevFest website: https://dublin-devfest-2018.firebaseapp.com/

Here's a little breakdown:

This year Dublin DevFest is being organised by a joint team of GDG Dublin and GDG Cloud Dublin

Dublin DevFest 2018 will have 10 speakers presenting 13 sessions on 20 technology topics!

Dublin DevFest 2018 take place on Saturday the 17th and Sunday 18th of November with the first day focusing on Talks and Codelabs and the second day held for an all-day hackathon!

Get your tickets for free here: https://www.eventbrite.ie/e/dublin-devfest-2018-tickets-51364812537
